   {:e #blake3 "ce3d5ad9c7cc631b49dfdd3de3b35aac679bf9780c9f22d451907057099c80f2" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Paired testing task for S045-L1-REV (entity_label additions) and S045-L2-REV (concept-level OAR).\n\nUNIT TESTS FOR S045-L1-REV (3 tests in routing.rs test module):\n\n1. test_entity_label_concept_name:\n   - Setup: Store with concept entity having :concept/name = 'error-handling', :concept/embedding, :concept/member-count.\n   - Assert: entity_label(store, concept_entity) == 'error-handling'.\n   - Verify: does NOT fall through to :db/ident or hex.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log all entity datoms and which attribute match fired.\n\n2. test_entity_label_pkg_stripped:\n   - Setup: Store with :db/ident = ':pkg/cascade' on an entity.\n   - Assert: entity_label(store, entity) == 'cascade' (not ':pkg/cascade').\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log the raw :db/ident value and the stripping logic path.\n\n3. test_entity_label_session_name:\n   - Setup: Store with :session/name = 'Session 045' on a session entity.\n   - Assert: entity_label(store, session_entity) == 'Session 045'.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log entity datoms showing :session/name exists but wasn't matched.\n\n4. test_entity_label_priority_ordering:\n   - Setup: Entity with BOTH :task/title AND :concept/name (unusual but possible).\n   - Assert: :task/title wins (it's higher in the priority chain).\n   - This verifies the insertion point is AFTER the human-text attributes.\n   ACTUALLY: :concept/name should be checked BEFORE :db/ident but AFTER :exploration/body/:task/title. Verify correct priority.\n\nUNIT TESTS FOR S045-L2-REV (4 tests in routing.rs test module):\n\n5. test_concept_observation_coverage_counts:\n   - Setup: Store with 10 observations in concept A, 3 in concept B (via :exploration/concept Refs), 5 from before last harvest.\n   - Assert: coverage[A] == 10 - (pre-harvest count), coverage[B] == 3 - (pre-harvest count).\n   - The harvest boundary must be respected (only count post-harvest observations).\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log all :exploration/concept Refs with their tx wall times vs harvest boundary.\n\n6. test_concept_dampening_formula:\n   - Assert: concept_dampening(entity, coverage={entity: 0}) == 1.2 (boost).\n   - Assert: concept_dampening(entity, coverage={entity: 3}) ~= 0.53.\n   - Assert: concept_dampening(entity, coverage={entity: 25}) ~= 0.12.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log formula parameters at each step.\n\n7. test_concept_oar_composes_with_namespace_oar:\n   - Setup: Task in namespace 'merge' with 3 observations AND nearest concept 'invariants' with 25 observations.\n   - Compute namespace factor (0.53) and concept factor (0.12).\n   - Assert: combined dampening ~= 0.53 * 0.12 ~= 0.064.\n   - Verify multiplicative composition is correct.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log both factors and the product.\n\n8. test_concept_oar_no_concepts_no_effect:\n   - Setup: Store with observations but no concepts (no :concept/embedding datoms).\n   - Assert: concept_dampening returns 1.0 (no effect) for all tasks.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log that concept scan found 0 concepts.\n\nE2E VERIFICATION:\n- After L1-REV + L2-REV land, run on Go CLI store:\n  braid status --verbose | grep 'bridge'\n  Verify bridge shows concept/session/pkg names, not raw idents.\n- Check braid guidance output shows concept-dampened routing.\n\nREGRESSION: cargo test -p braid-kernel -- routing:: (expect all 40+ routing tests pass + 8 new).\nDEPENDS-ON: S045-L1-REV (t-ea96e36c), S045-L2-REV (t-87ee8900)." :op :assert}
